cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DB

This paper discusses the development of access interfaces for digital repository and archival systems, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries), as the paper specifically mentions the Open Archive Initiative Protocol for Metadata Harvesting (OAI-PMH), which is a widely used protocol in digital library systems. The paper also discusses the NISO OpenURL Framework for Context-Sensitive Services, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and data management (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper may be of interest to researchers in the areas of cryptography (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG), as these fields are also relevant to digital repository and archival systems.
